That has angered Hughes, his former Manchester United team-mate.

‘Steve has fallen into the trap of trying to defend the indefensible,’ said Hughes. ‘Everyone has seen the two challenges and I don't think there is any sort of comparison whatsoever.

‘The outcome is there for everyone to see so I don't think Steve did himself too much credit with his observation.

‘It's fairly easily to defend things - and I do it too - but on this occasion it was not as if the lad would be suspended. So why did Steve not just say, “It was a terrible tackle”?

'We're trying to move on but Steve did not need to do that. He did not need to say that. To defend that is incorrect.’

